{
  "text": "According to the real estate tax optimization proposed above, we will no longer pay the land leasing in the development phase and cancel the land value increment tax that accounts for about 3% of the sales, so the land cost decrease to zero, meanwhile the real estate tax rate will decline [CITATION_1] . Assuming the tax rate reduced to 6.5%, the model simulations Compared to the actual data, it is not difficult to find that the prices are rising at a slow rate, and are lower than the actual data. Therefore, the optimization and the integration of real estate tax can limit the excessive growth of the real estate prices to a certain degree.",
